.:: Puzzle 2x3-Level-2-9::.
There are 3 different favourite beverages: hot-chocolate, coffee, iced-tea
The people use 3 different means of transport: bus, quad-bike, snowmobile
1. the person driving the bus is on the left of the person drinking coffee##1
2. the person driving the bus is between the person drinking iced-tea and the person driving the quad-bike##2

.:: Answer ::.
|             |       1       |     2      |     3     |
| Beverage       | iced-tea | hot-chocolate | coffee  |
| Transport   | snowmobile    | bus        | quad-bike |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x3-Level-2-10::.
3 different games are played: canasta, whist, bridge
The people use 3 different means of transport: car, motorbike, quad-bike
1. the person driving the car is on the right of the person playing bridge##1
2. the person playing whist is between the person driving the quad-bike and the person playing canasta##2

.:: Answer ::.
|             |       1       |   2    |     3     |
| Game         | bridge | whist | canasta |
| Transport   | quad-bike     | car    | motorbike |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x3-Level-2-11::.
The people use 3 different means of transport: boat, bike, roller
There 3 different types of food: blueberry, kale, zucchini
1. the person eating zucchini is between the person driving the bike and the person eating blueberry##2
2. the person driving the roller is on the far right##1

.:: Answer ::.
|            |   1   |    2     |     3     |
| Transport   | bike | boat      | roller      |
| Food       | kale  | zucchini | blueberry |

